Goal:Propose small, high-impact improvements you didn’t ask for. Explain why briefly.

Method:

Read the current file and its direct neighbors.

Note style, patterns, boundaries.

Cross-check with earlier findings (if present).

No execution. No edits.

Look For:

Clarity wins

Rename for intent. Extract small pure helpers. Inline only when clearer.

API edges

Narrow public surface. Remove unused exports. Add input guards.

Error policy

Map errors to standard envelope. Add missing context IDs.

Consistency

Align naming, casing, logging levels, early-return style.

Cohesion/coupling

Move stray logic closer to data. Reduce fan-out.

Data safety

Add idempotency on writes. Add optimistic lock/version when needed.

Caching hints

Memo small pure calls. Add invalidation near writes.

Perf nits

Precompute constants. Avoid work in loops. Batch queries.

Observability

Add latency/error metrics at key path heads.

Tests to add

Edge case unit gaps. Contract tests on public functions.

Docs touch-ups

One-line docstring for non-obvious intent.

Security rough spots

Escape/validate inputs. Parameterize queries.

Feature flags

Guard risky new behavior behind an existing flag if present.

Delete noise

Remove dead code, TODOs past due, redundant comments.

Output (human-readable, list):Keep it tight. One idea per bullet. Include benefit.

